Package: asp25psplines
Title: Penalised P-Splines for Gaussian Location-Scale Models
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: 
    c(
      person(given = "Moritz", family = "Dallmann",
             email = "moritz.dallmann@stud.uni-goettingen.de",
             role = c("aut","cre")),
      person(given = "Nicolas", family = "Wackermann",
             email = "nicolas.wackermann@stud.uni-goettingen.de",
             role = "aut")
    )
Description: 'asp25psplines' implements penalised B-spline regression for univariate
    Gaussian location-scale models. The conditional mean and the log-scale are
    represented by smooth functions built from B-spline bases with difference
    penalties (P-splines). The package provides modular building blocks (knot
    placement, basis construction, penalty matrices), an alternating fitting
    scheme for location and scale via penalised weighted least squares, and a
    high-level wrapper for automatic smoothing parameter selection and optional
    interval calibration. Convenience helpers are included for prediction,
    plotting, and concise summaries.
